    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-27T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-27T15:00:00-05:00" n="442"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d442">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 351.117/3.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Herrick</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-27T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 27, 1913, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Department informed by Senator Smoot concerning recent arrest in France for
                    military service of Joseph Nouguier. He was born at Moulins, France, June 24,
                    1884, emigrated to this country about December 5, 1903, and was naturalized as
                    American citizen February 14, 1912. He was appointed postmaster at San Rafael,
                    Utah, July 3, 1912. Senator Smoot has presented a petition of seventy citizens
                    of Utah for the release of Mr. Nouguier. Please present this matter to the
                    French Government and express the desire of this Government that it be made
                    possible for Mr. Nouguier to leave France and return to this country.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
